PRPO Lets roll NEW HAVEN Conn June 04 2019 GLOBE NEWSWIRE Specialty diagnostics company Precipio Inc NASDAQ PRPO announced that it has entered into an exclusive subcontracting manufacturing agreement with diagnostics manufacturing company Novamed for the production of Precipios proprietary IVCell media for an initial term of 3 years The agreement will provide Precipio with largescale production volume of the media enabling Precipio to provide cytogenetics laboratories in the US and worldwide with IVCell media to meet their demand Novamed is one of only a few companies worldwide with both substantial and specific experience in the production of products similar to IVCell and the manufacturing capabilities necessary to scale up production of the media in large volumes to meet customer demand as anticipated by Precipio

PRPO I can understand ppl loosing faith before today in this stock but I cant see it today The reagents and media that labs use to detect various disease is very expensive The lab is the most expensive let profitable department in a hospital I can tell you just to implement IT one machine in a hospital is anywhere from 1k to 2500 and that is just to install the interface I dont know how much these cost to implement bc I dont know the software they use I know reagents for the machines can run easily 10k a month depending on the testing required and the machine mechanisms that it entails I can also tell you that an exclusive deal is huge bc as that vendor goes to the labs to sell reagents and media to existing clients for media they currently produce they want a new slice of this pie now they will push this new media to every existing client they NovamedThis to me is the key because if Novamed didnt see ROI they would simply walk away from the deal

PRPO Here is why the manufacturer agreement is so important 1 Finding a properly licensed and structurally sound proprietary agreement with a company like Novamed is Key in securing future market share In order for hospital labs to comply the media company and reagents they supply must be held to the highest quality standards2 Having a trusted brand lends credibility to prpo brand which is not currently known widespread in the scientific lab market Novamed provides reagents and media to really big names such as Abbot which is a HUGE footprint in the medical lab space 3 When I talked to a rep from the company a while back they said they would not announce the manufacture until they had future customers that would justify the large scale manufacturer contract Looks like they now have enough to fulfill the orderMy suspicion is that they were looking for such a name to gain validity in this new space and finding a name such as Novamed is a great way to do just that
